# Implementation Plan: Overfit Recovery & Leakage Elimination

The current pipeline is suffering from a "Pseudo-Labeling Leakage Loop," where validation sets in the augmented training phase are contaminated with labels derived from the test set. This led to a deceptive 0.96964 OOF AUC while scoring only 0.95218 on the Kaggle Leaderboard.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> **Removing Pseudo-Labeling**: I am completely disabling the pseudo-labeling stage. While it can theoretically improve scores, our current implementation is causing more harm than good due to validation set contamination.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Conservative Training**: We will revert to training on the [train.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/train.csv) + `heart_disease_uci.csv` datasets only, ensuring the test set is strictly used for inference only.

## Proposed Changes

### Pipeline Refactoring
#### [MODIFY] [instrumented_pipeline.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/instrumented_pipeline.py)
- **Delete**: Remove the pseudo-labeling block (Lines 401-411).
- **Modify**: Update the final retraining phase to use only the clean augmented training set (original train + UCI).
- **Optimization**: Re-tune the ensemble blend weights (`alpha`) on the *clean* OOF predictions.
- **Complexity Reduction**: Clamp `iterations` to a more conservative range (e.g., max 3000) to prevent overfitting to UCI-specific noise.

